#: pages/code-tictactoc.php:79
msgid ""
"On dessine une grille de tic-tac-toc (3×3 = 9 cases). Chaque case est "
"<strong>divisée en 3 sections verticales</strong>. Les lettres remplissent "
"les sections de gauche à droite, case par case : A B C dans la case 1, D E F "
"dans la case 2, etc. La case 9 ne contient que Y et Z."
msgstr ""
"Draw a tic-tac-toe grid (3×3 = 9 squares). Each square is "
"<strong>divided into 3 vertical sections</strong>. The letters fill "
"the sections from left to right, square by square: A B C in square 1, D E F "
"in square 2, etc. Square 9 only contains Y and Z."

#: pages/code-tictactoc.php:80
msgid ""
"Le symbole = la <strong>forme de la case</strong> (ses bords dans la grille "
"#) + un <strong>point positionné</strong> dans la bonne section (gauche, "
"centre ou droite). C'est la <strong>position du point</strong> qui identifie "
"la lettre!"
msgstr ""
"The symbol = the <strong>shape of the square</strong> (its edges in the "
"# grid) + a <strong>positioned dot</strong> in the correct section (left, "
"center or right). It's the <strong>position of the dot</strong> that identifies "
"the letter!"

#: pages/code-tictactoc.php:83
msgid "La position du point est la clé :"
msgstr "The position of the dot is the key:"

#: pages/code-tictactoc.php:83
msgid ""
"Le point est placé à gauche (1re lettre), au centre (2e lettre), ou à droite "
"(3e lettre) à l'intérieur de la forme de la case. Un point centré ne "
"signifie PAS la même chose qu'un point à gauche!"
msgstr ""
"The dot is placed on the left (1st letter), in the center (2nd letter), or on the right "
"(3rd letter) inside the shape of the square. A centered dot does "
"NOT mean the same thing as a dot on the left!"

#: pages/code-tictactoc.php:87
msgid "Cliquez sur une lettre"
msgstr "Click on a letter"

#: pages/code-tictactoc.php:99
msgid ""
"M = case 5, point à gauche · I = case 3, point à droite · E = case 2, point "
"au centre · U = case 7, point à droite · X = case 8, point à droite"
msgstr ""
"M = square 5, dot on left · I = square 3, dot on right · E = square 2, dot "
"in center · U = square 7, dot on right · X = square 8, dot on right"

